    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Mojave Tan reads as a warm sienna in midday sun and a deep coffee at dusk. It is one of the more tonally responsive SKUs in the line and rewards homeowners who care about how a roof shifts color across the day.",
      "Look closely and you can pick out three or four granule shades inside the blend. The eye stops registering them at conversational distance, but the layered texture is why warm-brown asphalt roofs photograph as 'rich' rather than 'flat'.",
      "A natural choice if your house has brick or stone accents you want to tie the roof to. Stay clear of it on contemporary all-white builds where it can read as dated."
    ],
